Workspace workflow types : 
1. VCS driven : triggers run based on repository configuration changes
2. CLI driven : Triggers runs in a workspace using the terraform cli.
3. API driven : Triggers runs using the HCP Terraform cli.best for those with custom integrations and pipelines.

Execution modes in workspace settings : this is configured per workspace not on organizational level or project level.
-Project default
- remote : your plan & apply happens on HCP terraform infra. team can collaborate on runs within the app
- local : plan & apply runs on local machine. HCP terraform is used to store & sync the state
- agent : run your own lightweight agent to run terrafrm in isolated, private, on-premises infrastructure.

HCP Terraform teams and permissions

Access control hierarchy : 
Users : Can belong to multiple teams
Teams : Granted persmission at the org, project and workspace levels.
Permissions : Additive model : the highest permission always wins. Follow the principle of least privileges.

Team visibility : Visible and Secret
Team tokens : has the same level of access to the workspace as the team.

Organisational level : Broad permissions like manage all workspaces, manage policies, manage vcs settings, view all workspaces.
project level : Permissions scoped to a project and all workspaces within it ( Read, write, maintain and custom )
Workspace level : Permissions on a specific workspace such as admin , read, write, plan or custom.

PRIVATE REGISTRY : 
-----------------
using private modules using src address : app.terraform.io/<organisation-name>/terraform/<name>/<provider>
module "webapp" {
  source = app.terraform.io/////
  name = var.name
  prefix = var.prefix
  version = "1.0.0"
}

KEY TAKEAWAYS : 
  -  The private registry lets you share modules/providers privately within the org.
  -  u can also curate approved modules/providers alongside ur private ones.
  -  private modules are published from VCS repos and versioned with git TAGS .
  -  The source format includes Hostname : app.terraform.io/<organisation-name>/terraform/<name>/<provider>

Policy as Code : 
--------------
Codified rules : Securit, compliance and operational requirements written as code.
Version controlled : Stored in VCS , reviewed through pull requests just like infra code.
Automatically enforced  : Evaluated on every run, no manual review required.

Policy checks : 
-------------
  - Policy evaluate the plan data before any infra is created.
  - Failed policies can block the apply entirely.
  - Sentinel policy checks also have access to cost estimation data
  - If the plan itself fails, policies are never evaluated.















